<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-18T15:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-18T15:30:00-05:00" n="877" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3131/169: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-18T16:00:00-04:30">January 18, 1938—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5. My telegram No. 4 of January 18, 8 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d877fn3">Not printed.</note> Please telegraph when second announcement is to
                            be issued in the United States as the Venezuelan Government wishes to
                            make similar announcement here and publish the list of products on which
                            Venezuela will consider granting concessions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>